result.notes:
The dataset collected includes assessment output relating to the years from 
1905 to 2020 inclusive for the following variables for each stock: the annual 
recruitment estimate, the stock size (spawning stock biomass), landings 
(tonnes of fish brought to shore), catches (tonnes of fish caught at sea), 
fishing pressure (a fishing mortality rate), Fmsy (the target fishing 
mortality that will achieve maximum sustainable yield in the long term), Upper 
and lower range estimates for Fmsy consistent with multi-annual plans and 
ICES advice, MSYB trigger (a threshold for spawning stock biomass, below which 
fishing mortality should be reduced below Fmsy, following the ICES advice 
rule, to avoid reduced reproductive capacity, Blim (a lower limit threshold 
for spawning stock biomass below which there is a high risk of reduced 
reproductive capacity). The stock assessment data for fish and shellfish 
stocks of UK interest is used to assess indicators of reproductive capacity 
(based on spawning stock biomass) and fishing pressure (based on fishing 
mortality).
